StoryStack Privacy Policy

Last Updated: {{today’s date}}

StoryStack (“we”, “our”, “us”) provides tools that help users organize, tag, sequence, and export photos for social media content creation. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use the StoryStack mobile or web application (“the App”).

By creating an account or using the App, you agree to this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect
1.1. Account Information

When you create an account, we collect:

Email address

Password (securely hashed; we cannot view it)

1.2. User Content

When you use StoryStack, you may upload:

Photos

Story sequences

Titles, tags, and metadata you create

These are stored securely using our backend provider, Supabase.

1.3. Usage Information

We may collect basic, non-identifying usage information such as:

App version

Device type

Dates/times you access the app

No advertising or third-party tracking data is collected.

1.4. AI Tagging

If you choose to use auto-tagging:

Photos may be processed temporarily by our AI provider

Photos are not stored outside your account

They are used only to generate tags and are not used to train models

(If you prefer precise language for OpenAI vs Google Vision, I can tailor this more.)

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:

Provide core StoryStack functionality

Save and sync your photos, tags, and stories

Improve app performance and stability

Communicate with you about updates or support

Secure your account and detect misuse

We do not sell your data or share it with marketers.

3. How We Protect Your Information

We use industry-standard security measures including:

Encrypted connections (HTTPS/TLS)

Secure authentication

Hashed passwords

Row-Level Security through Supabase to isolate each user’s data

We restrict access so only you can see your uploaded content.

4. Sharing of Information

We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties except:

4.1. Service Providers

Only trusted vendors that help us operate StoryStack, such as:

Supabase (database and storage)

AI processing provider (optional auto-tagging)

These partners only access data needed to provide their service and are contractually prohibited from misuse.

4.2. Legal Requirements

We may disclose information if required to comply with:

Law enforcement requests

Court orders

Legal obligations

5. Your Rights and Choices

You may:

Access your account data

Update your information

Delete your account

Request deletion of stored photos and stories

Contact us at the email below for any such requests.

6. Data Retention

We retain your photos, tags, and stories for as long as your account remains active.
If you delete your account, we delete all associated user content from our storage systems within a reasonable period.

7. Children's Privacy

StoryStack is not directed at children under the age of 13.
We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.
If we discover such data, we will remove it promptly.

8. International Users

Your data may be stored and processed in the United States or other locations where our service providers operate.
By using the App, you consent to this processing.

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally.
If changes are significant, we will notify you via the App or email.

10. Contact Us

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, contact:

Email: support@storystack.app

(Use any email you prefer — I can modify this.)
